!! What it does

`rimir/mindmap-elixir` is a `module-type: mindmapengine` adapter that lets `rimir/mindmap` render via [[mind-elixir|https://github.com/SSShooter/mind-elixir-core]] (MIT-licensed, ~85 KB minified). The bundled mind-elixir core is v5.11.0.

!! Key features

* ''Drop-in adapter'' — install alongside `rimir/mindmap`; no configuration required if it's the only engine installed.
* ''Tree-native rendering'' — radial layout, expand/collapse, focus, drag, keyboard shortcuts.
* ''Op translation'' — mind-elixir's `operation` bus events are translated into the canonical Op vocabulary and appended to the view's overlay tiddler.
* ''Round-trip safe'' — unknown-namespace attrs (`mx:*`, `kn:*`, `cy:*`) survive the engine even when not rendered.
* ''Bundled library'' — mind-elixir IIFE + CSS shipped inside the plugin; no CDN or build step required.

!! What is mind-elixir?

A modern, tree-native mindmap library by [[SSShooter|https://github.com/SSShooter]]:

* MIT-licensed
* Active development (v5.11.0 released April 2026)
* Pluggable architecture with `me.install(plugin)`
* Built-in themes, custom CSS variable overrides
* Rich runtime API (`addChild`, `insertSibling`, `removeNode`, `bus.addListener("operation")`)

!! Prerequisites

* `$:/plugins/rimir/mindmap`
* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+

